header.gameNote: SAN JUAN SHOOTOUT AT SAN JUAN PR

article.headline: Appalachian State 87, Vanderbilt 79
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Donte Minter scored 27 points to lead Appalachian State to a 87-79 overtime victory over Vanderbilt in the San Juan Shootout championship game Thursday. The Mountaineers (10-3) outscored the Commodores 16-8 in overtime to clinch the tournament championship. In his fifth game for Appalachian State since transferring from Virginia, Minter shot 11-for-14 from the field and grabbed seven rebounds. D.J. Thompson added 15 points and seven rebounds, and Jeremy Clayton had 11 points. The Mountaineers beat a current Southeastern Conference opponent for the first time in 18 all-time meetings. Derrick Byars had 18 points for Vanderbilt (8-4) and Ross Neltner added 16 on 7-for-12 shooting. The Mountaineers trailed 40-38 at halftime and led 71-68 with 1:38 remaining. The Commodores' Alex Gordon tied the game with a 3-pointer with just over a minute remaining.
